==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Populin
<hw>Pop"u*lin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>populus</ets> poplar: cf. F. <ets>populine</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A glycoside, related to salicin, found in the
bark of certain species of the poplar (<gen>Populus</gen>), and
extracted as a sweet white crystalline substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

